---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Snapbyte"
  description="Understand how Snapbyte collects, stores, and secures your data. We prioritize your privacy and are committed to responsible data handling practices."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      This Privacy Policy outlines how Snapbyte ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, stores, and protects personal and technical data when you interact with our CDN caching infrastructure and associated services.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      Snapbyte primarily processes and caches user-generated or developer-supplied content. We may collect the following categories of information:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, authentication credentials.</li>
      <li><strong>Technical Metadata:</strong> IP addresses, browser types, device information, request headers, and usage logs collected during API or content delivery interactions.</li>
      <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Logs related to cache requests, origin fetches, content invalidation, and service errors.</li>
      <li><strong>Content Data:</strong> Files or assets delivered through Snapbyte CDN may be temporarily stored in our cache infrastructure depending on your caching policy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      We use your data to:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li>Deliver, operate, and improve Snapbyte’s CDN and caching performance</li>
      <li>Ensure security, availability, and performance of the file delivery system</li>
      <li>Provide customer support and respond to inquiries</li>
      <li>Communicate service updates, technical notices, and system alerts</li>
      <li>Detect, prevent, and mitigate fraud, abuse, and system misuse</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">3. Data Storage & Retention</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      Cached assets are stored temporarily based on your configuration (e.g., cache headers or manual purge commands). Logs and metadata are retained for diagnostic and analytics purposes, but minimized or anonymized where appropriate. We do not store content beyond its defined TTL unless otherwise agreed upon.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">4. Data Security</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      We employ industry-standard encryption, network segmentation, access control, and monitoring to protect your data. While we take strong precautions, no system is completely immune to vulnerabilities. We advise you to follow security best practices when using our platform.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">5. Third-Party Access</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      We do not sell or rent your personal information. However, we may share necessary information with:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li>Infrastructure providers (e.g., cloud platforms) strictly for service delivery</li>
      <li>Legal authorities when required by applicable law or court order</li>
      <li>Trusted third-party services for analytics, logging, or customer support, under strict data processing agreements</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">6. Your Rights & Choices</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      You have the right to:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li>Access and request a copy of your personal data</li>
      <li>Request correction or deletion of your data</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent or object to certain types of processing</li>
      <li>Request data portability, where applicable</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      To exercise these rights, please contact us via the information below. We may verify your identity before processing your request.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">7. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      Our infrastructure may operate globally. If data is transferred across jurisdictions, we ensure appropriate safeguards (such as Standard Contractual Clauses) are in place to protect your information in compliance with applicable regulations.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">8. Updates to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      This policy may be revised periodically. When we make changes, we will post the updated version with a revised “Last Updated” date. Significant changes may be communicated via email or platform notices.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">9. Contact Us</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      If you have questions about this policy or your data rights, contact us at:
      <br />
      <a class="text-blue-600 underline" href="mailto:support@snapbyte.com">support@snapbyte.com</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
